data.name: txtPassphrase.ToolTip
data.value: This is your secret token or passphrase. This value will be combined with the site name above to generate your final password. You can use the same pass- phrase here for all your sites, because the generated password will always be unique (since the site name must be unique). Obviously, the stronger this passphrase is, the stronger your final password will become.

data.name: gboxOptionalRules.ToolTip
data.value: This section contains optional settings or rules which allow you to modify the final password value. Here you can specify a password length, what characters will be used, and which hash algorithm to use to generate your new password. While the default values are usually OK, changing these can help adjust the value to better fit certain edge use cases.

data.name: cbCharLimit.ToolTip
data.value: This box allows you to restrict the length of your generated password. By default, Cryptnos will generate a password as long as the hash algorithm will produce. Many sites and applications, however, restrict the length of passwords to a set length. This field must either be "None" for no length restriction, or a whole number greater than one and less than the maximum length of the hash. Note that this limit is applied after the character type limit is applied, so it is possible to end up with a password shorter than the value you specify. Limits less than 8 will generate a warning as short passwords are extremely insecure.

data.name: txtIterations.ToolTip
data.value: This box contains the number of iterations of the hash algorithm to use while genera- ting your password. This must be a whole number greater than zero (positive integer). The default is 1, which is usually sufficient, but higher values create further distance between the input values and the final password. Higher values can also taken longer to generate on slower systems. Values higher than 500 will generate a warning, as they may be incompatible with versions of Cryptnos on other platforms.

data.name: cbHashes.ToolTip
data.value: This drop-down list contains the available cryptographic hash algorithms. You must select one. Stronger hashes will produce stronger passwords, but in general it doesn't matter which hash you use as long as you remain consistent for each individual password you generate. Note that the use of MD5 and SHA-1 are not recommended as these hashes have proven weak over time, but they are included for completeness and convenience.

data.name: cbCharTypes.ToolTip
data.value: This drop-down restricts the character types used in the final password. Some websites and applications restrict the types of characters you can use in a password. The algorithm used by Cryptnos to generate passwords may include characters that these sites won't like. In general, the safest value here is to use alphanumeric characters (letters and numbers), but it is strongly recommended to use all available characters if the site or application will allow it.

data.name: chkRemember.ToolTip
data.value: If this checkbox is checked, Cryptnos will remember your parameter information. IT WILL NEVER STORE YOUR PASSWORDS; only the parameters used to create them. Uncheck this box to make Cryptnos "forget" all of your parameters. Note that this checkbox may be disabled if you choose to lock your parameters.

data.name: txtPassword.ToolTip
data.value: This box will contain you final generated password. Enter your site name and passphrase above and click the Generate button to populate this box. You can then copy the value from this box and paste it into the password field for the site or application asking for the pass- word. Note that this field is read only and cannot be changed except by pressing the Generate button.

data.name: btnGenerate.ToolTip
data.value: Click this button to generate your password. Note that you must enter a site name and passphrase before this button will work. The generated password will be copied to the system clipboard. If Remember Parameters is checked and Lock Parameters is not checked, this will also save your parameters to the registry.

data.name: btnClose.ToolTip
data.value: Click this button to close Cryptnos. If you have chosen to remember your parameters, they will be written securely to the system registry at this time. You can also close Cryptnos by other traditional Windows methods, such as the "X" in the upper right corner of the window or by using Alt + F4.

data.name: cbSites.ToolTip
data.value: This field contains the "site name", a mnemonic or token that uniquely identifies the parameters for the password you are going to create. This can be a domain name or any other text that is easy for you to remember, but which must be unique for each password you generate.

data.name: btnImport.ToolTip
data.value: Click this button to import parameter infor- mation from a Cryptnos export file. You will be prompted for the location of the file and for the password you set during the export. Note that if the import file contains a site name that is already in your saved parameter list, the currently saved parameters WILL be overwritten with the information from the file.

data.name: btnForgetAll.ToolTip
data.value: Click this button to "forget" ALL parameter currently remembered. This will effectively clear all your saved information. Be sure this is what you actually want to do as this operation cannot be undone! This button will become disabled if the Remember Parameters checkbox is unchecked, or if the Lock Parameters checkbox is checked.

data.name: btnExport.ToolTip
data.value: Click this button to export one or more of your parameter entries to an external encrypted file. A dialog box will appear asking which set of parameters to export. You will also be prompted for a password that will be used to encrypt the export file. Export files can be used to copy password parameters from an instance of Cryptnos on one machine to an instance of Cryptnos on another machine, or to serve as a backup of your parameter data in case of current installation is damaged or lost.

data.name: btnForget.ToolTip
data.value: Click this button to "forget" the parameters for the site name currently selected in the Site Name drop-down above. Be sure this is what you really want to do as this operation cannot be undone! This button will become disabled if the Remember Parameters checkbox is unchecked, or if the Lock Parameters checkbox is checked.

data.name: gboxCoreParameters.ToolTip
data.value: This section contains the core required parameters for generating your pass- word. These are required, and Cryptnos will not work unless these values are specified. Your generated password will also be displayed here. You can fine tune your parameters further using the options in the sections below.

data.name: gboxRememberingSettings.ToolTip
data.value: This section allows you to specify if and how Cryptnos remembers your password para- meter information. Remember that YOUR PASSWORD IS NEVER SAVED; only the parameters used to generate it are remembered, and that information is ALWAYS encrypted. You can also make Cryptnos "forget" one or more of your parameters if you decide to discontinue their use.

data.name: chkLock.ToolTip
data.value: If this checkbox is checked, Cryptnos will lock your parameter information to prevent it from being modified or overwritten. In order to edit or "forget" parameter information, this box must be unchecked. Obviously, this implies that the Remember Parameters box must be checked for this box to be enabled. Checking this box disables that checkbox and the Forget, Forget All, and Import buttons.

data.name: chkShowTooltips.ToolTip
data.value: Clear this checkbox if you find these help tooltips to be annoying or no longer helpful. We certainly hope they WERE helpful, but if you know what you're doing, they sure can get in the way. If you ever want to bring them back, just check this box again and we'll be happy to help you once more.

data.name: chkCopyToClipboard.ToolTip
data.value: When this checkbox is checked, the generated password will be copied to the system clipboard as soon as it is created, saving you the step of copying it yourself. If unchecked, the password will not be copied to the clipboard.

data.name: btnAdvanced.ToolTip
data.value: This button lets you fiddle with the nuts-and-bolts settings behind the scenes. You really shouldn't mess with these unless you really know what you're doing, as it could "break" your existing passwords.

data.name: chkDailyMode.ToolTip
data.value: Check this box to enable "Daily Use" mode. In this mode, the Optional Rules, Remembering Settings, and other lower fields are hidden, leaving only the Core Parameters section visible. This makes Cryptnos much smaller and protects your settings for accidental change. Clear this box to restor the Cryptnos window to its full size.
